
CSS OverFlow
------------
overflow: visible
overflow: hidden
overflow: scroll
overflow: auto
overflow-x;
overflow-y;

visiable
--------

This is the default value. Any content that overflows the container will be visible.
 
Hidden
-------
Hidens any content that overflows the container.

scroll
-------
Scroll will add horizontal and vertical scroll bars even if content isn't larger than the container.

auto
-----
Auto will only add scroll bars when required it is usually the prefered option over scroll

overflow-x : It is controls the overflow content that flows horizontally (width)
overflow-y : It is controls the overflow content that flows vertically (height)
